{
  "meta": {
    "name": "Theater of Alexandria (FF9)",
    "id": "ff9-theater-alexandria",
    "colorScheme": "dual",
    "defaultScheme": "dark",
    "version": 1,
    "source": "Inspired by Final Fantasy IX: Alexandria stagecraft, storybook fantasy, and warm medieval charm",
    "tokenConvention": "Every color key maps to a CSS custom property named --<key>. e.g. \"accent\" -> var(--accent). The group names (surfaces, lines, text, accents, crystals, states) are for human organization only and are NOT part of the variable name. The four crystal-* tokens are extra identity colors; wire them up where supported.",
    "notExportedYet": "Non-color tokens still live only in styles.css and are intentionally omitted here: --radius, --radius-s, --shadow. FF9 can go further with playful ornament borders, hand-painted gradients, and slightly softer corner radii to echo storybook presentation."
  },
